BFN 

<F P=106> [By KRIM-TASS correspondent Olga Semenova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 26 TASS -- Heads of departments and 
regional bodies of the Federal Counter-intelligence Service met 
in Moscow today to attend a two-day all-Russia conference on 
problems of fighting organised crime, terrorism and drug 
business. 
  The conference is being attended by representatives from the 
Russian Interior Ministry, the prosecutor's office and other law 
enforcement bodies and secret services since problems put on the 
agenda require close interaction between these structures. 
  The conference will be addressed by Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin who will assess the work carried out by the federal 
counter- intelligence service and outline new tasks in the area 
of the activities of the counter-intelligence service. 

